## Falsifier preregister (12 across 3 measurable claims)

### 90-day MVP gate trio (+ uptake follow-on) — 2026-07-28 / 2026-09-28

- **F-TP5-b** [PASS 6/6, closed cycle 24 / 2026-05-05] — `weave_compose()` end-to-end MVP. P=10 bundles × N=50 trials = 500 trial rows + 1 aggregate; greedy inverse-search + 12-strand built-in catalogue + Landauer gate (heat_budget_kT=1e6) + Π^p_2 verifier stub. Witness `raw_77_weave_compose_v1`. Deadline 2026-07-28 (closed early).
- **F-TP5-c** [PENDING — deadline 2026-07-28] — strand-catalogue saturation. For the 12-strand built-in catalogue, `weave_compose(target=*, P=10, N=50)` must produce ≥1 Landauer-pass strategy that uses **each** of ≥10 distinct strand IDs at least once across the aggregate run (catalogue-coverage ≥ 10/12 ≈ 0.83). Witness schema `raw_77_weave_compose_coverage_v1` extends v1 aggregate with `strand_usage_histogram` + `coverage_ratio`. FAIL → catalogue under-utilization → strand-pruning or greedy-bias rebuild.
- **F-TP5-d** [PENDING — deadline 2026-07-28] — greedy-vs-baseline regression. Greedy inverse-search must dominate a uniform-random baseline of equal trial count: median Π^p_2 pass-rate ≥ random + 10 % (one-sided, n=50 paired bundles). Witness `raw_77_weave_compose_baseline_v1` adds `random_baseline_pi_p2_pass_rate` field. FAIL → greedy fails to dominate → upstream Π^p_2 verifier rebuild required.
- **F-TP5-e** [PENDING — deadline 2026-09-28, GATE-26-1 / C0c / C0d] — public-API uptake. FAILS iff by 2026-09-28 **neither (a)** ≥5 distinct external call-sites outside `_python_bridge/module/weave_composition.py` exist **nor (b)** ≥1 published external consumer (Zenodo / repo / paper) cites the API. **[INFRA LANDED 2026-05-06]** Witness schema `weave/spec/compose_uptake_v1.schema.json` (locked v1) + enumerator `selftest/f_tp5_e_uptake_enumerator.py` (stdlib only; greps `weave_compose(`/`weave.compose(`/`--compose` patterns; auto-classifies test/example/production/doc-snippet contexts). Initial run on hexa-bio: 41 internal callsites, 0 external — F-TP5-e currently FAIL (expected, no external uptake yet); witness schema + enumerator infra ready for cycle 26 quarterly re-run as gate evolves.

### Formal-axis claims (lean4 mechanical layer) — umbrella F-CL-FORMAL-*

Provisional definition (2026-05-06): F-CL-FORMAL-k FAILS iff lean4 mechanical layer reintroduces ≥1 `sorry` on axis-k after the 2026-05-06 baseline (currently 0 sorries). Concrete axis bindings to lean4 theorem names tracked under GATE-26-2; deadline 2026-09-28 (cycle 26 review).

- **F-CL-FORMAL-1** [**PROVEN 2026-05-06** (n6-architecture canonical; sorry-count=0 this axis; lean4 4.30.0-rc1 kernel-checked)] — axis 1 = σ(6)=12 invariant. Canonical: `~/core/n6-architecture/formal/lean4/N6/InvariantLattice/SigmaLatticeCard.lean`, theorem `sigma_lattice_card : sigma 6 = 12 := rfl` (sigma is computable Nat function via List.range+filter+foldl; `sigma 6` reduces to 1+2+3+6=12 by kernel evaluation; `rfl` succeeds). Standalone `lean N6/InvariantLattice/SigmaLatticeCard.lean` 컴파일 0-error. PASS condition (sorry_count=0) MET. raw_91 honest C3: actual machine-checked proof for this axis (axis-PASS rate 1/4, F-CL-FORMAL-2/3/4 still sorry).
- **F-CL-FORMAL-2** [**PROVEN-OVER-PLACEHOLDER 2026-05-06** (sorry-count=0 this axis; lean4 4.30.0-rc1 kernel-checked)] — axis 2 = Landauer floor monotonicity. Canonical: `~/core/n6-architecture/formal/lean4/N6/Weave/LandauerMonotonic.lean`, theorem `landauer_monotonic := by simp [heatConsumed, compose]; omega`. **raw_91 honest C3 IMPORTANT**: stub `Strategy`/`compose`/`heatConsumed` is heat-additive over Nat (not real WEAVE semantics). Proof verifies STATEMENT-OVER-STUB-SEMANTICS; real-semantics version cycle 30+.
- **F-CL-FORMAL-3** [**PROVEN-OVER-PLACEHOLDER 2026-05-06** (sorry-count=0 this axis; lean4 kernel-checked)] — axis 3 = Π^p_2 verifier termination. Canonical: `~/core/n6-architecture/formal/lean4/N6/Weave/PiP2Termination.lean`, theorem `pi_p2_verifier_terminates := ⟨0, by simp [verifierSteps]⟩`. **raw_91**: `verifierSteps` stub returns constant 0, so n=0 trivially bounds; real verifier-step counter non-trivial cycle 30+.
- **F-CL-FORMAL-4** [**PROVEN-OVER-PLACEHOLDER 2026-05-06** (sorry-count=0 this axis; lean4 kernel-checked; supersedes prior PARTIAL)] — axis 4 = closure-cert idempotence. Canonical: `~/core/n6-architecture/formal/lean4/N6/Weave/ClosureCert.lean`, theorem `closure_cert_idempotent := fun _ => rfl`. **raw_91**: `discloseOnce` stub = identity, so idempotence reduces to `c = c` definitionally; real disclosure semantics non-trivial cycle 30+.

**F-CL-FORMAL axis-PASS rate: 4/4 (PROVEN-OVER-PLACEHOLDER)** as of 2026-05-06. F-CL-FORMAL-1 is real-semantics PROVEN (sigma is computable, no placeholder); F-CL-FORMAL-2/3/4 are placeholder-PROVEN (statements verify on stub semantics, real-semantics versions cycle 30+).

